.TH "pdc_build_txd" 9 "pdc_build_txd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pdc_build_txd \- Build a DMA descriptor to transmit a SPU request to hardware.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pdc_build_txd
.BI "(struct pdc_state *pdcs "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dma_addr "  ","
.BI "u32 buf_len "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdcs" 12
PDC state for the SPU that will process this request
.IP "dma_addr" 12
DMA address of packet to be transmitted
.IP "buf_len" 12
Length of tx buffer, in bytes
.IP "flags" 12
Flags to be stored in descriptor
